						<div class="postbody">I'm writing an NES emulator in C++ and implemented every instruction for the 6502, accounting for cycles. I can run and pass many different 6502 test programs.<br /><br />For the last couple weeks, I've been trying to wrap my head around the PPU. I just don't seem to understand it. I think it might be related to the fact that I haven't actually written any NES roms.<br /><br />I'm thinking if I can write a couple simple ROMS I can maybe wrap my head around it. Is there any easy tutorials out that are recommended for emulator developers?<br /><br />Is this a good way of possibly fixing my dilemma so I can move on to the PPU?</div>

