				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If it's your first emulator, don't insist on getting everything perfect the first time. Make a basic PPU renderer. You'll need to get registers functional so the CPU will manipulate PPU memory so that you have something to actually draw on screen. Once you have that, you can make a basic render for single screen games like Donkey Kong just by drawing all the tiles in the nametable on screen, as well as the sprite list. <br /><br />You can work at making things more accurate as you go. By keeping it simple at first you can gain motivation and more importantly prevent hitting a wall and losing any motivation and giving up.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

